{"type":"message","id":"1fb780b6","parentId":"a770046d","timestamp":"2026-03-04T02:49:02.656Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"让我尝试 EODHD 的新闻 API，它可能可以工作并且可以提供新闻数据。我可以尝试执行它。","thinkingSignature":"617a8fc550b40a07c394893e1c9b5f5bcb4db015c5f01080ab8524a5e31882a6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bfukdwydvjcd_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST https://qveris.ai/api/v1/tools/execute \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $QVERIS_API_KEY\" \\\n  -d '{\"tool_id\": \"eodhd.news.retrieve.v1.fe8bf94c\", \"params\": {\"t\": \"stock\", \"limit\": 50}}'","timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":29651,"output":140,"cacheRead":13984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43775,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772592529948}}
{"type":"message","id":"c4279e3a","parentId":"1fb780b6","timestamp":"2026-03-04T02:49:10.952Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bfukdwydvjcd_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"execution_id\":\"e32feaf6-299e-4930-9180-0bb911567a32\",\"result\":{\"status_code\":200,\"message\":\"Result content is too long (266743 bytes). You can reference the truncated content (20480 bytes) and download the full content from the url provided.\",\"full_content_file_url\":\"http://qveris-tool-results-cache-bj.oss-cn-beijing.aliyuncs.com/tool_result_cache%2F20260304%2Feodhd.news.retrieve.v1.fe8bf94c%2F0c565ef9e7ba48db879b52712bc4c955.json?OSSAccessKeyId=LTAI5tM3qNRZSgSrg1iSTALm&Expires=1772599750&Signature=WI4Yct7v3Bb3VovmZOryqjoTcdM%3D\",\"truncated_content\":\"[{\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T02:31:28+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Tesla Rival Xiaomi Deploys Humanoid Robot With 3 Hours Of Autonomous Operating Time At EV Assembly Plant\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Xiaomi Corp has shared that it deployed humanoid robots in its EV assembly plant as the auto industry looks towards incorporating robotics into production activities.\\\\n\\\\n3 Hours Of Autonomous Operations\\\\n\\\\nThe Chinese tech giant shared that the humanoid robots it deployed successfully achieved 3 hours of autonomous operations, placing self-tapping nuts in the die-casting workshop, CnEVPost reported on Monday, citing a post on Chinese social media platform Weibo by Xiaomi.\\\\n\\\\nThe robots achieved a 90.2% success rate at the task, the report said. Xiaomi is reportedly considering other applications for its robots, which incorporate a Vision-Language-Action (VLA) approach combined with reinforcement learning.\\\\n\\\\nDon't Miss:\\\\n\\\\nExplore the Fire-Safe Energy Storage Company With $185M in Contracted Revenue This AI Helps Fortune 1000 Brands Avoid Costly Ad Mistakes — See Why Investors Are Paying Attention\\\\n\\\\nThe report also cited Xiaomi CEO Lei Jun, who, in a post on the Chinese social media platform WeChat, predicted that the tech company would see more humanoid robots being deployed at its production facilities in the next five years.\\\\n\\\\nRobotics And Chinese Auto Makers\\\\n\\\\nThe news comes as more auto manufacturers are entering the robotics sector, with Xpeng Inc. announcing that it was establishing a facility in Guangzhou, China, to target large-scale production of its IRON humanoid robot by the end of 2026.\\\\n\\\\nMeanwhile, Xpeng also aims to produce over 1 million units of the IRON robot by the end of the decade and has touted deploying the robot in sectors like tour guiding, retail services and more.\\\\n\\\\nSee Also: Own the Characters, Not Just the Content: Inside a Fast-Growing Pre-IPO IP Company\\\\n\\\\nTesla's Optimus, Boston Dynamics' Atlas\\\\n\\\\nTesla Inc. CEO Elon Musk also shared that the company faces its biggest competitive threat in the robotics sector from Chinese companies. Musk has been bullish on Tesla's Optimus, sharing that the robot could become the first-ever von Neumann probe and aid colonization efforts on other planets in Space.\\\\n\\\\nMusk had also shared plans to establish an Optimus Academy to train the robot by using Tesla’s reality generator. The Optimus academy would help Tesla train the robots using the same technology it uses for Full Self-Driving (FSD) training.\\\\n\\\\nTesla also faces competition from Hyundai Motor-backed Boston Dynamics, which recently shared details regarding its Atlas humanoid robot. The robot, according to the company, is scheduled to be deployed in the South Korean automaker’s production facility in Georgia.\\\\n\\\\nBoston Dynamics says Atlas is capable of lifting objects weighing up to 110 lbs and can function smoothly in temperature ranges from -4° to 104° F. It also boasts the capability of replicating a task learned by a single unit to the entire fleet.\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nRead Next:\\\\n\\\\n1.5 Million Users Are Already Working Inside This AI Platform — Investors Can Still Get In Blue-chip art has historically outpaced the S&P 500 since 1995, and fractional investing is now opening this institutional asset class to everyday investors.\\\\n\\\\nPhoto courtesy: Shutterstock\\\\n\\\\nUNLOCKED: 5 NEW TRADES EVERY WEEK. Click now to get top trade ideas daily, plus unlimited access to cutting-edge tools and strategies to gain an edge in the markets.\\\\n\\\\nGet the latest stock analysis from Benzinga:\\\\n\\\\nAPPLE (AAPL): Free Stock Analysis Report TESLA (TSLA): Free Stock Analysis Report\\\\n\\\\nThis article Tesla Rival Xiaomi Deploys Humanoid Robot With 3 Hours Of Autonomous Operating Time At EV Assembly Plant originally appeared on Benzinga.com\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/tesla-rival-xiaomi-deploys-humanoid-023128699.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"1810.HK\\\", \\\"AAPL.US\\\", \\\"TSLA.US\\\", \\\"WB.US\\\", \\\"XIACF.US\\\", \\\"XPEV.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"AUTO-INDUSTRY\\\", \\\"ROBOTICS\\\", \\\"TECH\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.99, \\\"neg\\\": 0.022, \\\"neu\\\": 0.88, \\\"pos\\\": 0.098}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T02:12:55+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Assessing Citigroup (C) Valuation After Morgan Stanley Endorsement And Profitability Push\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Find winning stocks in any market cycle. Join 7 million investors using Simply Wall St's investing ideas for FREE.\\\\n\\\\nMorgan Stanley’s recent endorsement of Citigroup (C) has put the bank back in focus for many investors, with attention centering on its profitability targets, cost reduction efforts, and potential shifts in market share.\\\\n\\\\nSee our latest analysis for Citigroup.\\\\n\\\\nCitigroup’s share price has eased in the past month, with a 30 day share price return of a 4.28% decline and a year to date share price return of a 6.69% decline. However, the 1 year total shareholder return of 57.07% and 3 year total shareholder return of about 1.4x highlight stronger longer term momentum as investors react to fresh fixed income issuance, recent conference activity and renewed interest following Morgan Stanley’s endorsement.\\\\n\\\\nIf this news has you thinking about what else could be moving the market, it might be a good moment to scan 18 top founder-led companies for fresh ideas beyond the big banks.\\\\n\\\\nWith Citigroup trading at $110.76 and screening on some models at roughly a 37% intrinsic discount and about 22% below the average analyst target, you have to ask: is this genuine value, or is the market already accounting for future gains?\\\\n\\\\nMost Popular Narrative: 4.5% Undervalued\\\\n\\\\nThe most followed narrative pegs Citigroup’s fair value at $116, a touch above the last close at $110.76. This frames a modest undervaluation tied to execution on its reorganisation and digital plans.\\\\n\\\\nCitigroup's global network is witnessing robust growth in cross-border transactions, U.S. dollar clearing, and demand for trade loans as corporates expand internationally; ongoing globalization and the complexity of capital flows are driving increased use of Citi's transaction services platform, supporting future growth in revenue and fee income.\\\\n\\\\nRead the complete narrative.\\\\n\\\\nCurious what kind of revenue mix, margin profile, and future valuation multiple need to line up for that $116 fair value to stack up? The full narrative spells out the growth pace, profit assumptions, and payout expectations that sit behind this call, and shows how small shifts in those inputs move the outcome. Result: Fair Value of $116 (UNDERVALUED)\\\\n\\\\nHave a read of the narrative in full and understand what's behind the forecasts.\\\\n\\\\nHowever, this depends on Citi maintaining its digital push and managing regulatory demands, which could increase costs and slow progress if they prove tougher than expected.\\\\n\\\\nFind out about the key risks to this Citigroup narrative.\\\\n\\\\nAnother Way To Look At Valuation\\\\n\\\\nOn earnings multiples, Citigroup looks less clear cut. It trades on a P/E of 14.9x, compared with 11.4x for the wider US Banks industry and 12.4x for peers, while our fair ratio sits higher at 16.2x. So is this a cushion, or a valuation trap if sentiment cools?\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nSee what the numbers say about this price — find out in our valuation breakdown.NYSE:C P/E Ratio as at Mar 2026\\\\n\\\\nNext Steps\\\\n\\\\nFeeling mixed after all of this? The best next step is to check the full picture for yourself, including the 4 key rewards and 1 important warning sign that investors are watching closely.\\\\n\\\\nLooking for more investment ideas?\\\\n\\\\nIf you stop with one bank, you could miss opportunities that suit your style better, so take a few minutes to see what else stands out right now.\\\\n\\\\nTarget consistent income by checking out 15 dividend fortresses, built for investors who want stronger yield potential and solid cash generation. Zero in on quality at a discount with 49 high quality undervalued stocks, highlighting companies where fundamentals and pricing currently look out of sync. Prioritise capital protection with 75 resilient stocks with low risk scores, focusing on businesses that score well on balance sheet strength and risk controls.\\\\n\\\\nThis article by Simply Wall St is general in nature. We provide commentary based on historical data and analyst forecasts only using an unbiased methodology and our articles are not intended to be financial advice. It does not constitute a recommendation to buy or sell any stock, and does not take account of your objectives, or your financial situation. We aim to bring you long-term focused analysis driven by fundamental data. Note that our analysis may not factor in the latest price-sensitive company announcements or qualitative material. Simply Wall St has no position in any stocks mentioned.\\\\n\\\\nCompanies discussed in this article include C.\\\\n\\\\nHave feedback on this article? Concerned about the content? Get in touch with us directly. Alternatively, email editorial-team@simplywallst.com\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/assessing-citigroup-c-valuation-morgan-021255744.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"C.US\\\", \\\"MS-PE.US\\\", \\\"MS-PF.US\\\", \\\"MS-PI.US\\\", \\\"MS-PK.US\\\", \\\"MS.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"BALANCE SHEET\\\", \\\"BANKS\\\", \\\"DIVIDENDS\\\", \\\"EARNINGS\\\", \\\"SHARE PRICE\\\", \\\"SHAREHOLDER\\\", \\\"VALUATION\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.998, \\\"neg\\\": 0.029, \\\"neu\\\": 0.816, \\\"pos\\\": 0.155}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T02:12:24+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Apple’s Broad Hardware Refresh Puts Ecosystem And Valuation In Focus\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Track your investments for FREE with Simply Wall St, the portfolio command center trusted by over 7 million individual investors worldwide.\\\\n\\\\nApple (NasdaqGS:AAPL) has rolled out a multi day hardware launch featuring the iPhone 17e, a redesigned iPad Air with the M4 chip, new MacBook Air and MacBook Pro models with M5 series chips, and the Studio Display XDR. The new Studio Display XDR includes features aimed at professional use cases, including medical imaging workflows. The products were introduced across several days, covering smartphones, tablets, laptops, and high end external displays. Apple highlighted advances in custom silicon, AI focused capabilities, and professional grade hardware as part of the rollout.\\\\n\\\\nFor you as an investor watching Apple, this kind of broad refresh across iPhone, iPad, Mac, and displays shows how central the hardware ecosystem remains to the NasdaqGS:AAPL story. Apple continues to operate across consumer devices and professional tools, with custom chips like the M4 and M5 series forming a core part of its product identity. The addition of features tailored to areas such as medical imaging also underlines Apple’s interest in specialised, higher end use cases.\\\\n\\\\nIn the period ahead, you may want to watch how buyers respond across each product line, from the entry level iPhone 17e to the Studio Display XDR aimed at professional environments. Adoption of AI related features and the new M series chips, along with any signals from Apple about user engagement across these devices, could be reference points for how this launch cycle fits into the broader NasdaqGS:AAPL story.\\\\n\\\\nStay updated on the most important news stories for Apple by adding it to your watchlist or portfolio. Alternatively, explore our Community to discover new perspectives on Apple.NasdaqGS:AAPL Earnings & Revenue Growth as at Mar 2026\\\\n\\\\nWe've flagged 0 risks for Apple. See which could impact your investment.\\\\n\\\\nInvestor Checklist\\\\n\\\\nQuick Assessment\\\\n\\\\n⚖️ Price vs Analyst Target: At about $263.75, Apple trades roughly 10% below the consensus price target of $293.29, which sits within the analyst range of $205 to $350. ⚖️ Simply Wall St Valuation: Apple is described as trading close to estimated fair value, so the current price does not screen as a clear discount or premium on this model. ✅ Recent Momentum: The 30 day return is about 1.6%, which is a mildly positive move as the new hardware cycle gets underway.\\\\n\\\\nThere is only one way to know the right time to buy, sell or hold Apple. Head to the Simply Wall St company report for the latest analysis of Apple's fair value.\\\\n\\\\nKey Considerations\\\\n\\\\n📊 This multi day refresh across iPhone, iPad, Mac, and Studio Display keeps Apple’s hardware ecosystem front and center, which is important given its role in driving usage of services and software. 📊 You might want to watch uptake of the M4 and M5 chips, AI focused features, and any commentary on how these devices influence revenue and earnings, which have been growing annually based on the provided figures. ⚠️ With a P/E of 32.88 versus an industry average of about 26.89, a key risk is that expectations embedded in the price may be high if the new products do not translate into the level of growth the market is anticipating.\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nDig Deeper\\\\n\\\\nFor the full picture including more risks and rewards, check out the complete Apple analysis. Alternatively, you can visit the community page for Apple to see how other investors believe this latest news will impact the company's narrative.\\\\n\\\\nThis article by Simply Wall St is general in nature. We provide commentary based on historical data and analyst forecasts only using an unbiased methodology and our articles are not intended to be financial advice. It does not constitute a recommendation to buy or sell any stock, and does not take account of your objectives, or your financial situation. We aim to bring you long-term focused analysis driven by fundamental data. Note that our analysis may not factor in the latest price-sensitive company announcements or qualitative material. Simply Wall St has no position in any stocks mentioned.\\\\n\\\\nCompanies discussed in this article include AAPL.\\\\n\\\\nHave feedback on this article? Concerned about the content? Get in touch with us directly. Alternatively, email editorial-team@simplywallst.com\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/apple-broad-hardware-refresh-puts-021224368.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"AAPL.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"AI\\\", \\\"EARNINGS\\\", \\\"HARDWARE\\\", \\\"PRICE TARGET\\\", \\\"PRICE-TARGET\\\", \\\"SEMICONDUCTORS\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.99, \\\"neg\\\": 0.015, \\\"neu\\\": 0.912, \\\"pos\\\": 0.073}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T02:11:00+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Bragar Eagel &amp; Squire, P.C. Urges CoreWeave, Inc. (NASDAQ:CRWV) Stockholders with Large Losses to Contact the Firm Before March 13th\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Bragar Eagel & Squire, P.C. Litigation Partner Brandon Walker Encourages Investors Who Suffered Losses In CoreWeave (CRWV) To Contact Him Directly To Discuss Their Options\\\\n\\\\nIf you purchased or acquired CoreWeave securities between March 28, 2025 and December 15, 2025, and would like to discuss your legal rights, call Bragar Eagel & Squire partner Brandon Walker or Melissa Fortunato directly at (212) 355-4648.\\\\n\\\\nClick here to participate in the action.\\\\n\\\\nNEW YORK, March  03, 2026  (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) --\\\\n\\\\nWhat’s Happening?\\\\n\\\\nBragar Eagel & Squire, P.C., a nationally recognized stockholder rights law firm, announces that a class action lawsuit has been filed against CoreWeave, Inc. (“CoreWeave” or the “Company”) (NASDAQ:CRWV) in the United States District Court for the District of New Jersey on behalf of all persons and entities who purchased or otherwise acquired CoreWeave securities between March 28, 2025 and December 15, 2025, both dates inclusive (the “Class Period”). Investors have until March 13, 2026 to apply to the Court to be appointed as lead plaintiff in the lawsuit.\\\\n\\\\nWhat are the Allegation Details?\\\\n\\\\nThe lawsuit alleges that Defendants issued false and misleading statements and/or failed to disclose that: (i) Defendants had overstated CoreWeave’s ability to meet customer demand for its service; (ii) Defendants materially understated the scope and severity of the risk that CoreWeave’s reliance on a single third-party data center supplier presented for CoreWeave’s ability to meet customer demand for its services; and (iii) the foregoing was reasonably likely to have a material negative impact on the Company’s revenue.\\\\n\\\\nWhat are the Next Steps?\\\\n\\\\nIf you purchased or otherwise acquired CoreWeave shares and suffered a loss, are a long-term stockholder, have information, would like to learn more about these claims, or have any questions concerning this announcement or your rights or interests with respect to these matters, please contact Brandon Walker or Melissa Fortunato by email at investigations@bespc.com, telephone at (212) 355-4648, or by filling out this contact form. There is no cost or obligation to you.\\\\n\\\\nAbout Bragar Eagel & Squire, P.C.:\\\\n\\\\nBragar Eagel & Squire, P.C. is a nationally recognized law firm with offices in New York, South Carolina, and California. The firm represents individual and institutional investors in securities, derivative, and commercial litigation as well as individuals in consumer protection and data privacy litigation. The firm has a nationwide practice and routinely handles cases in both federal and state courts. For more information about the firm, please visit www.bespc.com.  Attorney advertising.  Prior results do not guarantee similar outcomes.\\\\r\\\\nFollow us for updates on LinkedIn and Facebook, and keep up with other news by following Brandon Walker, Esq. on LinkedIn.\\\\n\\\\nContact Information:\\\\n\\\\nBragar Eagel & Squire, P.C.\\\\r\\\\nBrandon Walker, Esq.\\\\r\\\\nMelissa Fortunato, Esq.\\\\r\\\\n(212) 355-4648\\\\r\\\\ninvestigations@bespc.com\\\\r\\\\nwww.bespc.com\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/03/04/3249018/0/en/Bragar-Eagel-Squire-P-C-Urges-CoreWeave-Inc-NASDAQ-CRWV-Stockholders-with-Large-Losses-to-Contact-the-Firm-Before-March-13th.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"CRWV.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"BES\\\", \\\"BRAGAR EAGEL & SQUIRE\\\", \\\"BRANDON WALKER\\\", \\\"CLASS ACTION\\\", \\\"CLASS-ACTION\\\", \\\"COMPLAINT\\\", \\\"COREWEAVE\\\", \\\"CRWV\\\", \\\"DROP\\\", \\\"FRAUD\\\", \\\"INSTITUTIONAL INVESTORS\\\", \\\"INVESTOR\\\", \\\"LAW & LEGAL ISSUES\\\", \\\"LAWSUIT\\\", \\\"LOSS\\\", \\\"SHARES\\\", \\\"STOCK\\\", \\\"STOCKHOLDER-RIGHTS\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": -0.617, \\\"neg\\\": 0.087, \\\"neu\\\": 0.837, \\\"pos\\\": 0.076}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T02:10:12+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Schneider Electric Links AI Data Center Growth With Sustainability Focus\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Track your investments for FREE with Simply Wall St, the portfolio command center trusted by over 7 million individual investors worldwide.\\\\n\\\\nSchneider Electric, SK Telecom and Supermicro agreed to work together on modular AI data center solutions, targeting more scalable and efficient AI computing infrastructure. Schneider Electric also received an award recognizing its leadership in sustainable procurement practices.\\\\n\\\\nFor investors watching ENXTPA:SU, these moves add fresh context around a share price of €253.55 and a 3 year return of 72.9% and a 5 year return of 122.6%. The company is already well known for its role in energy management and automation, and this new AI data center focus broadens that industrial and digital footprint.\\\\n\\\\nThe tie up on AI data centers and the recognition for sustainable procurement both relate to how Schneider Electric is positioning itself in areas that matter for long term infrastructure and ESG minded capital. As these projects and practices develop, they may influence how you think about the balance between growth opportunities and sustainability credentials in any broader view of ENXTPA:SU.\\\\n\\\\nStay updated on the most important news stories for Schneider Electric by adding it to your watchlist or portfolio. Alternatively, explore our Community to discover new perspectives on Schneider Electric.ENXTPA:SU Earnings & Revenue Growth as at Mar 2026\\\\n\\\\nWe've flagged 1 risk for Schneider Electric. See which could impact your investment.\\\\n\\\\nThe AI data center partnership brings Schneider Electric closer to the fast growing compute build out, while the procurement award highlights how the company is trying to keep sustainability embedded in that growth. In practical terms, Schneider Electric contributes power, cooling and modular infrastructure, while SK Telecom and Supermicro bring AI workload expertise and servers. For you as an investor, this links the company’s traditional strengths in electrical equipment to a concrete use case in AI infrastructure, an area that also matters for peers such as ABB and Siemens.\\\\n\\\\nHow This Fits Into The Schneider Electric Narrative\\\\n\\\\nThe move into modular AI data centers lines up with the narrative’s focus on data center demand and digital services as key drivers for Schneider Electric’s long term earnings profile. The procurement award and increased AI focus also come with execution demands. This ties back to the narrative’s point that heavy inv\",\"content_schema\":{\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/schema#\",\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"date\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"title\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"content\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"link\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"symbols\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"tags\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"sentiment\":{\"anyOf\":[{\"type\":\"null\"},{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"polarity\":{\"type\":\"number\"},\"neg\":{\"type\":\"number\"},\"neu\":{\"type\":\"number\"},\"pos\":{\"type\":\"number\"}},\"required\":[\"neg\",\"neu\",\"polarity\",\"pos\"]}]}},\"required\":[\"content\",\"date\",\"link\",\"sentiment\",\"symbols\",\"tags\",\"title\"]}}},\"success\":true,\"elapsed_time_ms\":2733.04,\"cost\":6.5}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":8288,"aggregated":"{\"execution_id\":\"e32feaf6-299e-4930-9180-0bb911567a32\",\"result\":{\"status_code\":200,\"message\":\"Result content is too long (266743 bytes). You can reference the truncated content (20480 bytes) and download the full content from the url provided.\",\"full_content_file_url\":\"http://qveris-tool-results-cache-bj.oss-cn-beijing.aliyuncs.com/tool_result_cache%2F20260304%2Feodhd.news.retrieve.v1.fe8bf94c%2F0c565ef9e7ba48db879b52712bc4c955.json?OSSAccessKeyId=LTAI5tM3qNRZSgSrg1iSTALm&Expires=1772599750&Signature=WI4Yct7v3Bb3VovmZOryqjoTcdM%3D\",\"truncated_content\":\"[{\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T02:31:28+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Tesla Rival Xiaomi Deploys Humanoid Robot With 3 Hours Of Autonomous Operating Time At EV Assembly Plant\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Xiaomi Corp has shared that it deployed humanoid robots in its EV assembly plant as the auto industry looks towards incorporating robotics into production activities.\\\\n\\\\n3 Hours Of Autonomous Operations\\\\n\\\\nThe Chinese tech giant shared that the humanoid robots it deployed successfully achieved 3 hours of autonomous operations, placing self-tapping nuts in the die-casting workshop, CnEVPost reported on Monday, citing a post on Chinese social media platform Weibo by Xiaomi.\\\\n\\\\nThe robots achieved a 90.2% success rate at the task, the report said. Xiaomi is reportedly considering other applications for its robots, which incorporate a Vision-Language-Action (VLA) approach combined with reinforcement learning.\\\\n\\\\nDon't Miss:\\\\n\\\\nExplore the Fire-Safe Energy Storage Company With $185M in Contracted Revenue This AI Helps Fortune 1000 Brands Avoid Costly Ad Mistakes — See Why Investors Are Paying Attention\\\\n\\\\nThe report also cited Xiaomi CEO Lei Jun, who, in a post on the Chinese social media platform WeChat, predicted that the tech company would see more humanoid robots being deployed at its production facilities in the next five years.\\\\n\\\\nRobotics And Chinese Auto Makers\\\\n\\\\nThe news comes as more auto manufacturers are entering the robotics sector, with Xpeng Inc. announcing that it was establishing a facility in Guangzhou, China, to target large-scale production of its IRON humanoid robot by the end of 2026.\\\\n\\\\nMeanwhile, Xpeng also aims to produce over 1 million units of the IRON robot by the end of the decade and has touted deploying the robot in sectors like tour guiding, retail services and more.\\\\n\\\\nSee Also: Own the Characters, Not Just the Content: Inside a Fast-Growing Pre-IPO IP Company\\\\n\\\\nTesla's Optimus, Boston Dynamics' Atlas\\\\n\\\\nTesla Inc. CEO Elon Musk also shared that the company faces its biggest competitive threat in the robotics sector from Chinese companies. Musk has been bullish on Tesla's Optimus, sharing that the robot could become the first-ever von Neumann probe and aid colonization efforts on other planets in Space.\\\\n\\\\nMusk had also shared plans to establish an Optimus Academy to train the robot by using Tesla’s reality generator. The Optimus academy would help Tesla train the robots using the same technology it uses for Full Self-Driving (FSD) training.\\\\n\\\\nTesla also faces competition from Hyundai Motor-backed Boston Dynamics, which recently shared details regarding its Atlas humanoid robot. The robot, according to the company, is scheduled to be deployed in the South Korean automaker’s production facility in Georgia.\\\\n\\\\nBoston Dynamics says Atlas is capable of lifting objects weighing up to 110 lbs and can function smoothly in temperature ranges from -4° to 104° F. It also boasts the capability of replicating a task learned by a single unit to the entire fleet.\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nRead Next:\\\\n\\\\n1.5 Million Users Are Already Working Inside This AI Platform — Investors Can Still Get In Blue-chip art has historically outpaced the S&P 500 since 1995, and fractional investing is now opening this institutional asset class to everyday investors.\\\\n\\\\nPhoto courtesy: Shutterstock\\\\n\\\\nUNLOCKED: 5 NEW TRADES EVERY WEEK. Click now to get top trade ideas daily, plus unlimited access to cutting-edge tools and strategies to gain an edge in the markets.\\\\n\\\\nGet the latest stock analysis from Benzinga:\\\\n\\\\nAPPLE (AAPL): Free Stock Analysis Report TESLA (TSLA): Free Stock Analysis Report\\\\n\\\\nThis article Tesla Rival Xiaomi Deploys Humanoid Robot With 3 Hours Of Autonomous Operating Time At EV Assembly Plant originally appeared on Benzinga.com\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/tesla-rival-xiaomi-deploys-humanoid-023128699.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"1810.HK\\\", \\\"AAPL.US\\\", \\\"TSLA.US\\\", \\\"WB.US\\\", \\\"XIACF.US\\\", \\\"XPEV.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"AUTO-INDUSTRY\\\", \\\"ROBOTICS\\\", \\\"TECH\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.99, \\\"neg\\\": 0.022, \\\"neu\\\": 0.88, \\\"pos\\\": 0.098}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T02:12:55+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Assessing Citigroup (C) Valuation After Morgan Stanley Endorsement And Profitability Push\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Find winning stocks in any market cycle. Join 7 million investors using Simply Wall St's investing ideas for FREE.\\\\n\\\\nMorgan Stanley’s recent endorsement of Citigroup (C) has put the bank back in focus for many investors, with attention centering on its profitability targets, cost reduction efforts, and potential shifts in market share.\\\\n\\\\nSee our latest analysis for Citigroup.\\\\n\\\\nCitigroup’s share price has eased in the past month, with a 30 day share price return of a 4.28% decline and a year to date share price return of a 6.69% decline. However, the 1 year total shareholder return of 57.07% and 3 year total shareholder return of about 1.4x highlight stronger longer term momentum as investors react to fresh fixed income issuance, recent conference activity and renewed interest following Morgan Stanley’s endorsement.\\\\n\\\\nIf this news has you thinking about what else could be moving the market, it might be a good moment to scan 18 top founder-led companies for fresh ideas beyond the big banks.\\\\n\\\\nWith Citigroup trading at $110.76 and screening on some models at roughly a 37% intrinsic discount and about 22% below the average analyst target, you have to ask: is this genuine value, or is the market already accounting for future gains?\\\\n\\\\nMost Popular Narrative: 4.5% Undervalued\\\\n\\\\nThe most followed narrative pegs Citigroup’s fair value at $116, a touch above the last close at $110.76. This frames a modest undervaluation tied to execution on its reorganisation and digital plans.\\\\n\\\\nCitigroup's global network is witnessing robust growth in cross-border transactions, U.S. dollar clearing, and demand for trade loans as corporates expand internationally; ongoing globalization and the complexity of capital flows are driving increased use of Citi's transaction services platform, supporting future growth in revenue and fee income.\\\\n\\\\nRead the complete narrative.\\\\n\\\\nCurious what kind of revenue mix, margin profile, and future valuation multiple need to line up for that $116 fair value to stack up? The full narrative spells out the growth pace, profit assumptions, and payout expectations that sit behind this call, and shows how small shifts in those inputs move the outcome. Result: Fair Value of $116 (UNDERVALUED)\\\\n\\\\nHave a read of the narrative in full and understand what's behind the forecasts.\\\\n\\\\nHowever, this depends on Citi maintaining its digital push and managing regulatory demands, which could increase costs and slow progress if they prove tougher than expected.\\\\n\\\\nFind out about the key risks to this Citigroup narrative.\\\\n\\\\nAnother Way To Look At Valuation\\\\n\\\\nOn earnings multiples, Citigroup looks less clear cut. It trades on a P/E of 14.9x, compared with 11.4x for the wider US Banks industry and 12.4x for peers, while our fair ratio sits higher at 16.2x. So is this a cushion, or a valuation trap if sentiment cools?\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nSee what the numbers say about this price — find out in our valuation breakdown.NYSE:C P/E Ratio as at Mar 2026\\\\n\\\\nNext Steps\\\\n\\\\nFeeling mixed after all of this? The best next step is to check the full picture for yourself, including the 4 key rewards and 1 important warning sign that investors are watching closely.\\\\n\\\\nLooking for more investment ideas?\\\\n\\\\nIf you stop with one bank, you could miss opportunities that suit your style better, so take a few minutes to see what else stands out right now.\\\\n\\\\nTarget consistent income by checking out 15 dividend fortresses, built for investors who want stronger yield potential and solid cash generation. Zero in on quality at a discount with 49 high quality undervalued stocks, highlighting companies where fundamentals and pricing currently look out of sync. Prioritise capital protection with 75 resilient stocks with low risk scores, focusing on businesses that score well on balance sheet strength and risk controls.\\\\n\\\\nThis article by Simply Wall St is general in nature. We provide commentary based on historical data and analyst forecasts only using an unbiased methodology and our articles are not intended to be financial advice. It does not constitute a recommendation to buy or sell any stock, and does not take account of your objectives, or your financial situation. We aim to bring you long-term focused analysis driven by fundamental data. Note that our analysis may not factor in the latest price-sensitive company announcements or qualitative material. Simply Wall St has no position in any stocks mentioned.\\\\n\\\\nCompanies discussed in this article include C.\\\\n\\\\nHave feedback on this article? Concerned about the content? Get in touch with us directly. Alternatively, email editorial-team@simplywallst.com\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/assessing-citigroup-c-valuation-morgan-021255744.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"C.US\\\", \\\"MS-PE.US\\\", \\\"MS-PF.US\\\", \\\"MS-PI.US\\\", \\\"MS-PK.US\\\", \\\"MS.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"BALANCE SHEET\\\", \\\"BANKS\\\", \\\"DIVIDENDS\\\", \\\"EARNINGS\\\", \\\"SHARE PRICE\\\", \\\"SHAREHOLDER\\\", \\\"VALUATION\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.998, \\\"neg\\\": 0.029, \\\"neu\\\": 0.816, \\\"pos\\\": 0.155}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T02:12:24+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Apple’s Broad Hardware Refresh Puts Ecosystem And